#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:5
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Overview"

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:7
msgid ""
"Climweb is a Django-based web application with Wagtail CMS integration, "
"designed for use by National Meteorological and Hydrological Services "
"(NMHSs) in their content management and deliver of climate information and "
"services."
msgstr ""
"Climweb is a Django-based web application with Wagtail CMS integration, "
"designed for use by National Meteorological and Hydrological Services "
"(NMHSs) in their content management and deliver of climate information and "
"services."

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:10
msgid ""
"The system is designed to be modular and extensible, allowing for easy "
"addition of new features and content types. It is built with a focus on "
"customization and flexibility, enabling NMHSs to tailor the system to their "
"specific needs."
msgstr ""
"The system is designed to be modular and extensible, allowing for easy "
"addition of new features and content types. It is built with a focus on "
"customization and flexibility, enabling NMHSs to tailor the system to their "
"specific needs."

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:13
msgid "Web Framework & CMS"
msgstr "Web Framework & CMS"

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:15
msgid "Built on Django framework with Wagtail CMS integration"
msgstr "Built on Django framework with Wagtail CMS integration"

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:16
msgid ""
"Uses ASGI (Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface) for modern web "
"capabilities"
msgstr ""
"Uses ASGI (Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface) for modern web "
"capabilities"

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:17
msgid ""
"The system Implements both WSGI and ASGI configurations for flexibility"
msgstr ""
"The system Implements both WSGI and ASGI configurations for flexibility"

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:19
msgid "Backend Architecture"
msgstr "Backend Architecture"

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:21
msgid ""
"The backend architecture section describes the core components of Climweb's "
"backend."
msgstr ""
"The backend architecture section describes the core components of Climweb's "
"backend."

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:23
msgid "Pages/Apps structure"
msgstr "Pages/Apps structure"

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:25
msgid ""
"The pages/apps structure section provides an overview of how the pages/apps "
"are organized within Climweb, using the conventional Django app structure."
msgstr ""
"The pages/apps structure section provides an overview of how the pages/apps "
"are organized within Climweb, using the conventional Django app structure."

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:30
msgid ""
"The extending Climweb section discusses how to extend the functionality of "
"Climweb by creating custom plugins, which add more features and capabilities"
" to the system."
msgstr ""
"The extending Climweb section discusses how to extend the functionality of "
"Climweb by creating custom plugins, which add more features and capabilities"
" to the system."

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:33
#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:1
msgid "Management Commands"
msgstr "Management Commands"

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:35
msgid ""
"Climweb provides a set of management commands that can be used to perform "
"various tasks related to the system's operation and maintenance."
msgstr ""
"Climweb provides a set of management commands that can be used to perform "
"various tasks related to the system's operation and maintenance."

#: ../../_docs/technical/index.md:38
msgid ""
"The management commands section provides an overview of these commands and "
"their usage."
msgstr ""
"The management commands section provides an overview of these commands and "
"their usage."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:3
msgid "Resetting login attempts and lockouts"
msgstr "Resetting login attempts and lockouts"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:5
msgid ""
"Climweb uses [Django Axes](https://django-axes.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) to"
" manage login attempts and lockouts."
msgstr ""
"Climweb uses [Django Axes](https://django-axes.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) to"
" manage login attempts and lockouts."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:7
msgid "An account is locked when a user has failed to login too many times."
msgstr "An account is locked when a user has failed to login too many times."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:9
msgid ""
"![Climweb locked account](../../_static/images/technical/locked-account.png "
"\"Climweb locked account\")"
msgstr ""
"![Climweb locked account](../../_static/images/technical/locked-account.png "
"\"Climweb locked account\")"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:9
msgid "Climweb locked account"
msgstr "Climweb locked account"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:11
msgid ""
"This means that the instructions on Django Axes' documentation for resetting"
" login attempts and lockouts are applicable to Climweb as well."
msgstr ""
"This means that the instructions on Django Axes' documentation for resetting"
" login attempts and lockouts are applicable to Climweb as well."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:14
msgid ""
"When Axes locks an IP address, it is not allowed to login again. You can "
"allow IPs to attempt again by resetting ( deleting) the relevant "
"AccessAttempt records in the admin UI, or Command Line Interface (CLI)."
msgstr ""
"When Axes locks an IP address, it is not allowed to login again. You can "
"allow IPs to attempt again by resetting ( deleting) the relevant "
"AccessAttempt records in the admin UI, or Command Line Interface (CLI)."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:17
msgid "Resetting attempts from the Django admin UI"
msgstr "Resetting attempts from the Django admin UI"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:19
msgid "Records can be easily deleted by using the Django admin application."
msgstr "Records can be easily deleted by using the Django admin application."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:21
msgid ""
"Go to the django admin UI and check the Access Attempt view. Select the "
"attempts you wish the allow again and simply remove them. The blocked user "
"will be allowed to log in again in accordance to the rules."
msgstr ""
"Go to the django admin UI and check the Access Attempt view. Select the "
"attempts you wish the allow again and simply remove them. The blocked user "
"will be allowed to log in again in accordance to the rules."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:24
msgid ""
"On Climweb, the default URL path for the Django admin UI is `/dj-ad-admin/`."
" This can be changed in the settings file using the variable "
"`DJANGO_ADMIN_URL_PATH`."
msgstr ""
"On Climweb, the default URL path for the Django admin UI is `/dj-ad-admin/`."
" This can be changed in the settings file using the variable "
"`DJANGO_ADMIN_URL_PATH`."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:27
msgid "Resetting attempts from the CLI"
msgstr "Resetting attempts from the CLI"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:29
msgid ""
"Django Axes offers a command line interface with `axes_reset`, "
"`axes_reset_ip`, `axes_reset_username`, and `axes_reset_ip_username` "
"management commands with the Django manage.py or django-admin command "
"helpers:"
msgstr ""
"Django Axes offers a command line interface with `axes_reset`, "
"`axes_reset_ip`, `axes_reset_username`, and `axes_reset_ip_username` "
"management commands with the Django manage.py or django-admin command "
"helpers:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:32
msgid ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset` will reset all lockouts and access records."
msgstr ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset` will reset all lockouts and access records."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:33
msgid ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset_ip [ip ...]` will clear lockouts and records "
"for the given IP addresses."
msgstr ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset_ip [ip ...]` will clear lockouts and records "
"for the given IP addresses."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:34
msgid ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset_username [username ...]` will clear lockouts "
"and records for the given usernames."
msgstr ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset_username [username ...]` will clear lockouts "
"and records for the given usernames."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:35
msgid ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset_ip_username [ip] [username]` will clear "
"lockouts and records for the given IP address and username."
msgstr ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset_ip_username [ip] [username]` will clear "
"lockouts and records for the given IP address and username."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:37
msgid ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset_logs` (age) will reset (i.e. delete) AccessLog "
"records that are older than the given age where the default is 30 days."
msgstr ""
"`python manage.py axes_reset_logs` (age) will reset (i.e. delete) AccessLog "
"records that are older than the given age where the default is 30 days."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:40
msgid ""
"Resetting attempts from the CLI in a Climweb Docker Compose environment"
msgstr ""
"Resetting attempts from the CLI in a Climweb Docker Compose environment"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:42
msgid ""
"On a production Climweb instance, to clear all lockouts and access records, "
"run the following command:"
msgstr ""
"On a production Climweb instance, to clear all lockouts and access records, "
"run the following command:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:50
msgid "This is a shorthand command that does the following:"
msgstr "This is a shorthand command that does the following:"

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:52
msgid ""
"`cd climweb` changes the working directory to the Climweb project directory."
msgstr ""
"`cd climweb` changes the working directory to the Climweb project directory."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:53
msgid ""
"`docker compose exec climweb /bin/bash` runs a bash shell in the `climweb` "
"container."
msgstr ""
"`docker compose exec climweb /bin/bash` runs a bash shell in the `climweb` "
"container."

#: ../../_docs/technical/management-commands.md:54
msgid ""
"`climweb axes_reset` runs the `axes_reset` command in the Climweb container."
msgstr ""
"`climweb axes_reset` runs the `axes_reset` command in the Climweb container."

